Here's the PlantUML sequence diagram for the control flow in `kryptokrauts_ae-prediction-cards`:

```plantuml
@startuml kryptokrauts_ae-prediction-cards
actor User
participant Frontend
participant WalletClient
participant PredictionCardsApi
participant SmartContract
participant OracleService
participant ProcessPredictionService
database Blockchain

User -> Frontend: Create Prediction (asset, price, times, images)
Frontend -> WalletClient: Sign transaction
WalletClient -> SmartContract: create_prediction()
SmartContract -> Blockchain: Store prediction data
SmartContract --> WalletClient: Transaction receipt
WalletClient --> Frontend: Confirmation
Frontend --> User: Prediction created

User -> Frontend: Rent NFT (outcome, deposit, price)
Frontend -> WalletClient: Sign transaction
WalletClient -> SmartContract: rent_nft()
SmartContract -> Blockchain: Update NFT rental state
SmartContract --> WalletClient: Transaction receipt
WalletClient --> Frontend: Confirmation
Frontend --> User: NFT rented

ProcessPredictionService -> Blockchain: Monitor for CLOSED predictions
Blockchain --> ProcessPredictionService: Prediction end time reached
ProcessPredictionService -> SmartContract: ask_for_winning_option()
SmartContract -> OracleService: Oracle query
OracleService -> ExternalAPI: Get asset price
ExternalAPI --> OracleService: Current price
OracleService -> SmartContract: process_oracle_response(price)
SmartContract -> Blockchain: Store winning outcome
SmartContract --> ProcessPredictionService: Result processed

User -> Frontend: Claim rewards
Frontend -> WalletClient: Sign transaction
WalletClient -> SmartContract: claim()
SmartContract -> Blockchain: Verify longest renter
SmartContract -> Blockchain: Transfer NFT ownership
SmartContract -> Blockchain: Distribute rewards
SmartContract --> WalletClient: Transaction receipt
WalletClient --> Frontend: Confirmation
Frontend --> User: Rewards claimed
@enduml
```